                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/8344</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Blocker</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Eagle Pass</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-10T16:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 10, 1917—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following telegram received from Consul O’Hea at Gomez Palacio: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Dangerous trip overland but arrived safely finding conditions secure but
                            difficult. Most of Americans and other foreigners saved themselves by
                            proving other nationality. There is [no] doubt but that departure saved
                            American lives.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blocker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
